<package name="pacemaker" project="openSUSE:Factory">
  <title>The Pacemaker scalable High-Availability cluster resource manager</title>
  <description>Pacemaker is an advanced, scalable High-Availability cluster resource
manager for Linux-HA (Heartbeat) and/or OpenAIS.

It supports &quot;n-node&quot; clusters with significant capabilities for
managing resources and dependencies.

It will run scripts at initialization, when machines go up or down,
when related resources fail and can be configured to periodically check
resource health.</description>
